==Abilities==
<!-- The power list and levels has been carefully reviewed and approved with the media released as of Agent Carter Season One. DO NOT MAKE arbitrary changes to them or it may lead to blocks. If something is wrong, please contact WikiProjects: Powers & Abilities -->
*'''Expert Marksman''': When going into battle, Dugan often brought and efficiently used a revolver and shotgun, but also used other firearms with relative ease. Gaining multiple kills against [[Hydra]] and [[Leviathan]] soldiers, he proved himself to be an expert marksman before and after [[World War II]]. He routinely helped [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]] by shooting the enemies with his shotgun.
*'''Tactician''': Dugan assumed leadership of the [[Howling Commandos]] following [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]]'s supposed death, through missions in [[Russia]]. As their leader, he strategized their next moves and even had a plan to help [[Peggy Carter]] and [[Jack Thompson]], before collaborating to make a better one.

==Equipment==
===Weapons===
*'''{{WPS|M1917 revolver|Colt M1917 Revolver}}''': [[File:Dugan1917.jpg|thumb|250px|Dugan providing cover fire for [[Peggy Carter]]]] Dugan carried a revolver as his sidearm, getting to use it as he ambushed [[Hydra]] Forces with the rest of the [[Howling Commandos]] during the [[Attack on Hydra Headquarters]]. He also carried it to the [[Red Room Academy]] in the [[Soviet Union]], but [[Eva]] took it from him and used it to kill [[Junior Juniper]].
*'''{{WPS|Thompson submachine gun#M1928A1|M1928A1 Thompson}}''': One of the standard firearms of the [[United States Army]] during [[World War II]]. Dugan was issued one of these, and he used to battle German forces during the [[Attack at Azzano]].
*'''{{WPS|Winchester 1897}}''': Dugan carried this shotgun as his weapon of choice, and he used it during the [[Howling Commandos]]' raids on [[Hydra]] facilities and during the [[Attack on Hydra Headquarters]]. He continued to use it during [[World War II]] as he worked together with [[Peggy Carter]] to raid the [[Hydra Research Facility Number 4]].
*'''{{WPS|Winchester Model 1912|Winchester Model 1912 Trench Gun}}''': [[File:Dugan-Shoots-Iron-Ceiling.jpg|thumb|250px|Dugan aiming at several [[Leviathan]] soldiers]] Following the end of [[World War II]], Dugan traded his shotgun for a similar model, and it was the weapon he carried to investigate the [[Red Room Academy]] in the [[Soviet Union]] with [[Peggy Carter]], engaging in a shootout against [[Leviathan]] soldiers.
*'''{{WPS|Mk 2 grenade|Mk 2 Grenade}}''': Dugan usually carried a couple of hand grenades, and was about to use one inside the [[Red Room Academy]], when [[Eva]] tricked him and killed one of Dugan's [[Junior Juniper|teammates]]. However, [[Peggy Carter]] stopped him, believing Eva was just a girl.
*'''[[Arnimhilation 99L Assault Weapon]]''': Dugan grabbed one of [[Hydra]]'s weapons during his [[Liberation of Allied Prisoners of War|escape]] from the [[Hydra Base Camp C3]].

===Other Equipment===
{{Quote|You alright?"<br>"Yeah, the vest took the brunt of it.|[[Peggy Carter]] and Dum Dum Dugan|The Iron Ceiling}}
*'''Bulletproof Vest''': Dugan wore a vest on many of his missions, including one he undertook with [[Peggy Carter]] to investigate the [[Red Room Academy]]. The vest protected him when [[Eva]] stabbed him.
*'''[[Axel Grease]]''': [[Peggy Carter]] gave Dugan a bottle of Axel Grease as payment for helping her infiltrate the [[Red Room Academy]]. Dugan later gave the bottle to [[Johann Fennhoff|Viktor Ivchenko]] after rescuing him from the academy.

==Facilities==
*'''[[Whip & Fiddle]]''': As a famous pub in [[London]] among the Allied troops, Dugan and his [[Howling Commandos]] team hang out in the pub and even inform [[Steve Rogers]] that [[Howard Stark]] wanted him to test new equipment.
*'''[[Strategic Scientific Reserve Headquarters]]''': When [[Arnim Zola]] started revealing [[Red Skull]]'s motivations and goals, Dugan visited the Strategic Scientific Reserve Headquarters and join in the devised plan to attack [[Hydra]]'s [[Hydra Headquarters|Headquarters]].
*'''[[Stark Mansion]]''': On a holiday, Dugan visited [[Howard Stark]]'s mansion and sat by him while looking at a woman in a bikini that he felt aroused upon.

===Prisons===
*'''[[Hydra Base Camp C3]]''': Dugan was held prisoner in a [[Hydra]] weapons facility and forced to do labor and was tormented by the guards. Dugan was later freed by [[Steve Rogers]], and helped Rogers continue attacking the facility as he and the rest of the [[107th Infantry Regiment]] escaped together.

